news.title: Redevelopment along Chennai MRTS to cost less
news.para: Tamil Nadu Housing and Urban development department has made the amendment in the Tamil Nadu Combined Development and Building Rules, 2019, to bring these two corridors under the TOD. This is expected to benefit development along the existing MRTS corridor that runs across the city along a 19.7 km corridor between Chennai Beach and Velachery with 17 stations.

news.title: Dharavi TDR rule will make implementation of DP 2034 hard: BMC
news.para: In a draft notification issued in November last year, the state proposed that builders seeking to use additional floor space index (FSI) in the form of TDR must first use DRP TDR.

news.title: TOD policy since 2017 in Haryana, but little impact on the ground
news.para: Areas within 800m of a mass rapid transport system (MRTS) are considered TOD zones in the state. As of now, such zones are along the metro tracks in Gurgaon and Faridabad.

news.title: New regulations for apartment governance in Karnataka
news.para: State authorities collaborate on a comprehensive act to modernise apartment governance, streamline regulations, and enhance maintenance

news.title: Special scheme hope for small homes on Kolkata fringes
news.para: Developers also said introduction of a targeted scheme for affordable segment homes would propel development in areas like Joka, Sonarpur and Rajarhat.

news.title: Delhi HC calls city 'slum', says authorities must work together against illegal construction
news.para: Asking the authorities to stop passing the buck to one another, a bench headed by Acting Chief Justice Manmohan said, "Very sad affairs you have reduced the city to."

news.title: India Cements posts net loss of Rs 7 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Revenue from operations was at Rs 1,144.46 crore during the period under review. It was Rs 1,281 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.

news.title: ED searches India Cements offices in FEMA probe
news.para: The searches were launched on Wednesday at two office premises of the company in Chennai and one in Delhi, under the provisions of the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA)

news.title: Somany Ceramics posts profit of Rs 23.40 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Somany Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 614.95 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 1.85 per cent from Rs 626.51 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: India's Prism Johnson posts a net profit of Rs 1.78 crore in Q3 FY 24
news.para: The cement and tiles maker said its net profit after tax came in at 17.8 million rupees ($214,537.96) for the quarter ended Dec. 31, compared to a loss of 447.4 million rupees in the year-earlier period. This was the company's fourth straight quarterly profit.

news.title: Interim Budget 2024: A roadmap for inclusive development and economic resilience
news.para: The budgetary measures strategically focus on key sectors such as urban and rural housing, infrastructure, and transportation, indicating a concerted effort to stimulate economic growth while addressing the diverse needs of society.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 25.50% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 326.64 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 10.80 per cent from Rs 294.80 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Orient Electric's net profit dips 25.28% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Orient Electric's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 756.21 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 1.14 per cent from Rs 747.65 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Karnataka government to digitise land records to check fraud deals
news.para: The initiative, Bhu Suraksha, is set to be launched within a month, starting with one taluk in each of the 31 districts, minister Krishna Byregowda said Wednesday. This strategic move, while ensuring transparency and efficiency in maintaining land records, will also allow easy accessibility to those records.

news.title: Government to launch scheme to help middle class buy or build own house: Finance minister
news.para: Parallely, she also announced building 2 crore more houses for the rural poor in the next five years under the continuing PM Awas Yojana (Grameen).

news.title: Raymond's net profit increases by 91.92% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Raymond's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,450.32 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 11.40 per cent from Rs 2,199.53 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Country Garden looks to sell its $570 million residential development in London
news.para: Property agent Knight Frank said it had been appointed by Risland UK - a subsidiary of Country Garden - to market the 1,000-home Calico Wharf development, where construction has yet to start, in the Poplar area of the city.

news.title: Delhi HC pulls up MCD officials for failing to act against illegal construction
news.para: A bench headed by Acting Chief Justice Manmohan "warned" the officials, who were present in court, and questioned how the construction activity was permitted to go on in spite of an earlier order directing removal of illegal structures there as well as a 'work stop' notice.
